import React, { useEffect, useRef } from 'react'; import { ThreeScene } from '../utils/ThreeScene'; import './About.css'; function About() { const containerRef = useRef(null); const sceneRef = useRef(null); useEffect(() => { if (containerRef.current && !sceneRef.current) { sceneRef.current = new ThreeScene(containerRef.current); sceneRef.current.createParticles(100); sceneRef.current.createFloatingMesh(); } return () => { if (sceneRef.current) { sceneRef.current.dispose(); sceneRef.current = null; } }; }, []); return (

Our Philosophy

Intelligence for cities that lead.

Why This Exists

Cities face interconnected challenges: environmental stress, health system strain, food security threats. Traditional approaches treat these separately. We believe they must be understood together.

This system exists to reveal those connections, model interventions, and empower leaders to act with confidence.

How We Think

Systems thinking. Data-driven. Human-centered. We believe intelligence should be:

  • Clear, not overwhelming
  • Actionable, not academic
  • Humble about uncertainty
  • Focused on outcomes

What We Value

Clarity over complexity. Insight over information. Action over analysis paralysis. We design for leaders who need to understand risk, model futures, and make decisions.

Core Principles

◆

Interconnected

Environmental, health, and food security risks are deeply connected. We model those connections.

◆

Real-Time

Risks emerge and evolve. Our system monitors continuously, revealing changes as they happen.

◆

Predictive

We don't just show what is. We model what could be, enabling proactive decision-making.

◆

Transparent

Every insight is grounded in data. Every recommendation is explainable. Trust through clarity.

Our Vision

A world where cities understand risk before it emerges, simulate outcomes before acting, and lead with confidence backed by intelligence.

); } export default About;
